      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 9-month-old male infant is brought to the outpatient department presenting with mental retardation, delayed developmental milestones, and jaundice. Laboratory investigations reveal elevated unconjugated bilirubin and hypoglycemia (RBS &ndash; 40 mg/dl). Additionally, the urine analysis indicates aminoaciduria. The infant has been exclusively breastfed and has experienced recurrent vomiting and diarrhea since birth. Based on these findings, what is the most likely diagnosis?</span></span></span></p>",
